verbose_text: We identified a significant relationship between paternal age and all sperm parameters analyzed : for every 5 years of age, sperm volume decreases by 0.22 ml (P < 0.001), concentration increases by 3.1 million sperm/ml (P = 0.003) and percentage motile spermatozoa decreases by 1.2% (P < 0.001).
evidence: age, sperm volume decreases by 0.22 ml
